  "title": "Spa Therapist (Part Time)",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Perform all treatments at an exceptional standard, as per the protocols and standards taught in training, whilst tailoring to the guest's specific needs</li>\n  <li>Update own knowledge of products and treatment brand standards, outside of training</li>\n  <li>Carry out an in-dept consultation with each guest prior to treatment, ensuring medical history and concerns are identified</li>\n  <li>Maintain linen and product leves in the treatment roos, ensuring cabinets are stocked, clean and organised as per the spa standards</li>\n  <li>Ensure aftercare recommendations are made at the end of every treatment, linking with guest concerns and offering to prepare products at reception for purchase</li>\n  <li>Consistently record guest's preferences, accurately updating guest profiles and communication any relevant information to colleagues</li>\n  <li>Perform treatments in a professional, hygienic and safe manner for all guests, updating knowledge and training regularly</li>\n  <li>Responsible for the cleanliness, sterilisation and hygiene of all equipment, products and linens in the treatment and preparation areas, following the brand protocols</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Relevant certification in Spa Services</li>\n  <li>At least 1 year of relevant experience</li>\n  <li>Excellent communication and interpersonal skills</li>\n  <li>Willing to work shift hours including weekends, and public holidays</li>\n</ul>",
